The project is currently organized around three main tracks.

# Track Pages

* [RISC-V zkVM Track](/project/tracks/riscv-zkvm/)
* [EVM Track](/project/tracks/evm/)
* [Cryptography Track](/project/tracks/cryptography/)

This split is intended to scale. Each track can eventually grow from a short summary into a small documentation area with:

* current status pages
* artefact and repository links
* grant-linked outcomes
* notes on methodology and open questions

# Current Summaries

## RISC-V zkVM Track

Verify the arithmetization of RISC-V zkVMs. Ensure polynomial constraints exactly encode RISC-V instruction semantics based on the official Sail RISC-V specification.

## EVM Track

Show that an EVM running on RISC-V correctly implements the EVM specification. Focus on performant implementations compilable to RISC-V zkVMs.

## Cryptography Track

Verify the specification, proofs of security, and implementation of proof systems and cryptographic primitives used by zkVMs.
